{
  "texts": [
    "The overall summary of how IoT improves agricultural efficiency is provided in the Table 3.",
    "According to Farooq et al. (2022), IoT-based climate control systems in greenhouses have been shown to increase crop yields by 15% and reduce energy costs by 10%.",
    "Additionally, Zhang et al. (2018) reported that precision farming techniques using IoT result in an average 20% increase in crop yield compared to traditional farming.",
    "Furthermore, Li and Niu (2020) found that automation and IoT systems can reduce the need for manual labor, resulting in up to a 30% decrease in labor costs.",
    "Finally, Mahdavinejad et al. (2018) stated that IoT technology helps optimize resource allocation and reduce waste, leading to a 15-20% reduction in overall operational costs."
  ]
}